DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       This manual page describes the GNU version of ttrrooffff.  It is part of the
       groff document formatting system.  It is functionally  compatible  with
       Unix  troff,  but  has  many extensions, see ggrrooffff__ddiiffff(7).  Usually it
       should be invoked using the ggrrooffff(1) command which will also  run  pre-
       processors  and  postprocessors  in  the appropriate order and with the
       appropriate options.

